        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 5:28PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Royalton, or near Christopher, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Herrin, West Frankfort, Benton, Johnston City, Christopher, Zeigler,
Royalton, Hurst, Buckner, Orient, Freeman Spur, and Bush.

This includes Interstate 57 in Illinois between Mile Markers 59 and
71.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
